mlvpn (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add IPv6 support to the mlvpn0 TUN interface: tunnel.address6 (an
    optional IPv6 CIDR) assigns a second address family to the same
    device alongside the existing IPv4 tunnel.address, sharing the same
    encrypted session and bonded links. The underlying UDP transport
    between mlvpnd instances is still IPv4-only (see ARCHITECTURE.md
    §11 item 4); this is dual-stack payload, not dual-stack transport.
  * Add adaptive tunnel MTU: each bonded link's real physical interface
    MTU is queried via SIOCGIFMTU at bind time (link.rs), and
    tunnel.mtu is now treated as an upper bound rather than a fixed
    value -- main.rs's effective_tunnel_mtu() auto-clamps it down (with
    a logged warning) if it would fragment against the smallest
    detected physical MTU, turning the previous startup-only advisory
    warning into a real, self-correcting default.
  * Add TCP MSS clamping (mss.rs), on by default via the new
    tunnel.clamp_mss config option: rewrites the MSS option of TCP
    SYN/SYN-ACK segments (IPv4 and IPv6) transiting the tunnel to fit
    the effective tunnel MTU, avoiding the "PMTUD black hole" failure
    mode where a network silently drops the ICMP messages TCP would
    otherwise use to discover the right segment size on its own.
  * Add ARCHITECTURE.md's "Relationship to the original MLVPN" section:
    credits zehome/MLVPN (Laurent Coustet) for the bonding/monitoring/
    failover concept this project is a from-scratch Rust rewrite of,
    and documents the specific reasons for the rewrite (binds to a
    network interface rather than an IP address so it survives DHCP/
    roaming changes, memory-safe implementation, Noise_IK handshake
    with forward secrecy instead of a shared password, and more).

 -- Jeff Parrish PC Services <www.jpps.us>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

mlvpn (0.1.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * security: bump ratatui 0.29 -> 0.30, pulling in a patched lru
    (>= 0.16.3) that fixes a soundness issue in lru's IterMut affecting
    versions >= 0.9.0, < 0.16.3 (RUSTSEC advisory). ratatui 0.29 pins
    lru = "0.12.0", which cargo resolved to the vulnerable 0.12.5; a
    Cargo [patch] can't bridge that semver-incompatible pre-1.0 gap, so
    following ratatui's own dependency bump was the only real fix.
    lru is only ever reachable via mlvpn-tui (the monitoring binary);
    mlvpnd's core/data-path code doesn't depend on it. Reviewed
    ratatui's 0.30 breaking changes against src/bin/mlvpn-tui.rs's
    actual usage (no block::Title, Style/Stylize, Alignment, Marker, or
    generic Backend exposure) -- no source changes needed there, but
    default-features trimmed in Cargo.toml to avoid pulling in an
    unused `time` dependency from 0.30's new all-widgets default.
  * Raise minimum supported Rust toolchain to 1.86 (from 1.75), which
    ratatui 0.30 itself requires.
  * Audited every crate in Cargo.lock with a published RustSec
    advisory against our actual locked version (tokio, bytes, rand,
    tracing-subscriber, ring, time, snow, curve25519-dalek, aes-gcm,
    nix, zerocopy, hashbrown); all already resolve to patched versions
    under the existing Cargo.toml semver ranges, no further pins
    needed beyond the lru fix above.
  * Fix release.yml's RPM build (rockylinux9 leg): rpmbuild's internal
    BuildRequires check can't see the rustup-installed toolchain and
    failed with "cargo/rust >= 1.75 is needed" regardless of version;
    added rpmbuild -ba --nodeps, same reasoning as the .deb build's
    dpkg-buildpackage -d.
  * Fix RPM packaging failing with "Empty %files file
    debugsourcefiles.list": Cargo.toml's strip = true leaves no debug
    symbols for rpmbuild's find-debuginfo to extract. Added
    %global debug_package %{nil} to packaging/rpm/mlvpn.spec.

